                <head>No. 206.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wing</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito, Ecuador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2, 1873</date>. (Received December
                        30.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 347.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Since the reception of dispatch No. 126 from the
                    Department, I have had an interview with Minister Leon, who stated to me that
                    thus far all efforts to discover the perpetrators of the outrage upon the
                    Protestant cemetery near this city had proved unavailing.</p>
                <p>He added that the search was still being prosecuted, and promised that the
                    severest penalties would be inflicted upon the miscreants, in case of their
                    eventual capture.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>RUMSEY WING.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
